A Certified USDA Organic Farm & CO-OP including a Food Hub. Our mission is Nutritional Living & Healing with Local, Regional, National, the Americas and Sustainable Products. We do not obtain produce nor products from stores. What we do not grow certified organic, we deal with farmers directly and organic wholesalers in order to offer a full line of Certified Organic Produce and Products & sustainable.

We offer certified organic produce, fruits, grains vegetables grown in the State of Alabama, Regional, Nationally, The Americas and locally including many other organic products such as nuts, butters, breads, cheeses, coffees, herbs, mushrooms, citrus, honey, packaged foods, cider vinegars, nectar, sauces, quail and chicken eggs, John Ellis Miracle Water, essential oils, toothpaste, soaps, laundry detergents, loofahs, organic green bags and much more. We have added Organic Nutritional Healing and Energy Technology Healing Products. This is the way to overall heath we are offer.

listing_desc: Field to Family works to create a more local, healthy and sustainable community-based food system in the Iowa City/ Cedar Rapids region. Field to Family is a nonprofit local food hub offering farm to school education, serving multiple school districts, the University of Iowa, food access agencies, local businesses and other institutions in east central Iowa as well as individual residents and households by increasing access to- and demand for- healthy and local foods. The organization works in partnership with 30+ food service professionals, 60+ local farmers and value - added agricultural enterprises to procure, store, promote and deliver locally-grown foods and food products while ensuring food safety, freshness and quality.
